For the Chiles it’s easier to boil the water with them in it. Look for a change in color. Don’t strain it there is no need lol it’s soup.
Also Julian good loads cool those tortillas more.
He had green Chiles in the beginning which we add lol. For those you want to grill and burn them all around open flame. Then you put them in a plastic bag right off the grill and let them cool in the closed bag. They will easily peel. Then you can add too the soup 😋

snippet.textDisplay: I hope it’s ok if I give a tip for straining the adobo. Since it’s going to go into the pot and become a more liquid consistency anyway, you can take some liquid from the pot and thin it out to strain it more easily. That way all the smooth adobo and liquid from the pot will end up in your container that will get dumped back into the pot! Hope that helps someone!

snippet.textDisplay:
Looks so rich and delicious, congrats on nailing it :)

Lil tip for your tortillas: you need to turned them 3 times so their "pancita" rises up, kinda like a pocket with one of layers becoming thinner than the other.

Once you lay the tortilla in the pan as soon you can slide it (stops being sticked to the pan like 10 seconds.)
Then you flip it and leave it like a minute ( depends on the heat) and you do one final flip and poke it gently.......see how they rise and blow up
snippet.textOriginal:
